The emir of Maradun, Sarkin Kaya, Alhaji Garba Mohammad Tambari, has said that the death of the chief of staff to President Muhammadu Buhari, Mallam Abba Kyari leaves a huge vacuum that is very difficult to fill. The royal father who expressed shock over his death,  described the late Chief of Staff as very loyal, committed and dedicated aide to President Muhammadu Buhari. In a statement, signed by Ibrahim Magaji Dosara yesterday, Tambari further said it is worrisome that Mallam Abba, an experienced administrator, died at the time when he was needed the most, by the President and the Presidency. According to him, “his demise will create vacuum not only in the office he occupied, but also leaves us with unimaginable thinking about the contagious and debilitating effect of this global pandemic.” The emir, therefore, on behalf of his family, the Emirate Council and the entire people of Maradun Emirate condoles with President Muhammadu Buhari, Federal Government of Nigeria, Nigerians and the families of the late Chief of Staff to the President, Malam Abba Kyari. “We pray fervently and earnestly for the repose of his soul. “May the Almighty Allah grant Mallam Abba Kyari Jannatul Firdaus and give President Muhammadu Buhari and the beloved family of the deceased the fortitude to bear the irreparable loss,” he said.  